Subject: [PATCH 0058/2588] drm/i915: handle failure path correctly for lvds

In failure path, make sure encoder is cleaned up, otherwise there
is a kernel oops.

Signed-off-by: Shaohua Li <shaohua.li@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Eric Anholt <eric@anholt.net>
(cherry picked from commit 1991bdfaf5897b6fbfdc7dce81508f7cbc044768)

Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_lvds.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_lvds.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_lvds.c
index 789590f..c6984f3 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_lvds.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_lvds.c
@@ -1190,5 +1190,6 @@ failed:
 	if (intel_output->ddc_bus)
 		intel_i2c_destroy(intel_output->ddc_bus);
 	drm_connector_cleanup(connector);
+	drm_encoder_cleanup(encoder);
 	kfree(intel_output);
 }
